text: Austral thrush (Turdus falcklandii) is a common bird found in southern South America. It has a brown head. Its breast is gray-yellow. Its beak is solid and yellow. It has dark brown eyes with yellow eyebrows. It has a hard voice == Other websites == * IUCN red list * Austral thrush in Chilean and Falklands postages Category:Thrushes Category:Birds of South America
